                "content": "---\nname: chatgpt-remote-image-service\ndescription: Use when the user wants to submit reference-image generation jobs to the remote ChatGPT image HTTP service, poll task status, or get a public R2 image URL from the hosted endpoint. Trigger for requests involving remote ChatGPT 生图接口, 公网生图服务, chatgpt-image.vyibc.com, remote image generation API, taskId polling, or CLI calls to the image service.\n---\n\n# ChatGPT Remote Image Service\n\nUse this skill for the hosted ChatGPT image queue service.\n\nDefault endpoint:\n\n```text\nhttps://chatgpt-image.vyibc.com\n```\n\nThe service is public and does not require an Authorization header. Object names are made unique by the service: if the caller sends `uploadName=test.png`, the final R2 object will use the task id, such as `<taskId>.png`, to avoid overwriting prior images.\n\nThe service supports both modes:\n\n- Reference-image generation: send `image` and `prompt`.\n- Reference-image generation from URL: pass `--imageUrl` to the CLI, or download the URL first for raw HTTP.\n- Pure prompt generation: send only `prompt`.\n\n## Quick Start\n\nPrefer the bundled CLI:\n\n```bash\nscripts/chatgpt-remote-image.sh \\\n  --imageUrl \"https://resource.vyibc.com/reference.png\" \\\n  --prompt \"以参考图中的人物为准，生成一张在游泳馆的照片\"\n```\n\nLocal reference file:\n\n```bash\nscripts/chatgpt-remote-image.sh \\\n  --image /path/to/reference.png \\\n  --prompt \"以参考图中的人物为准，生成一张在游泳馆的照片\"\n```\n\nPure prompt generation:\n\n```bash\nscripts/chatgpt-remote-image.sh \\\n  --prompt \"生成一张未来城市夜景照片，真实摄影风格\"\n```\n\nThe script submits `POST /generate`, polls `GET /tasks/<taskId>`, and exits successfully only when `publicImageUrl` is returned.\nAt startup it also prints the current browser worker summary, including total workers, logged-in workers, workers requiring login, active workers, queued tasks, and CDP ports.\nIf\n...[truncated for Node Builder]"
